          <div><div>  <a href="/blog/literary-tributes/farewell-adam-zagajewski-marek-makowski" hreflang="und"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/medium_thumbnail/public/blog/literary-tributes/zagajewskiadammakowski-w.jpg?itok=rPwSmwt0" width="250" height="175" alt="A black and white photograph of Adam Zagajewski. A row columns stretches out behind him" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-medium-thumbnail" />

</a>

</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><p class="field-content"><a href="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/literary-tributes/farewell-adam-zagajewski-marek-makowski">A Farewell to Adam Zagajewski</a>
</p></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-author"><span class="views-label views-label-field-author field-name-field-blogauthor">By</span><span class="field-content field-name-field-blogauthor"><a href="/author/marek-makowski" hreflang="en">Marek Makowski</a>
</span></div>
        </li>
          </ul>
  </div>
      <a data-jcarousel-control="true" data-target="-=3" class="jcarousel-control-prev" href="#"></a>
    <a data-jcarousel-control="true" data-target="+=3" class="jcarousel-control-next" href="#"></a>
